            "name": "backstory",
            "value": "Kira Sterling\u2019s life has been a study in synthesis. Born in a Sacramento suburb to a Black Air Force mechanic and a White high school librarian, she spent her youth navigating the space between worlds. This constant code-switching sharpened her powers of observation, making her preternaturally skilled at reading people and situations\u2014a talent that led her to pursue a journalism degree at UC Berkeley. She dreamed of uncovering truths and telling the stories that mattered.\n\nHer early career as a reporter was thrilling but financially precarious. The turning point came during the dot-com bust of the early 2000s when, laid off from a local paper, she took a temporary job in market research to pay the bills. There, she discovered a new kind of storytelling. Instead of sources, she had data; instead of headlines, she had actionable insights. She found she could predict narratives before they happened. The stability and intellectual challenge were seductive. Over the next two decades, she methodically climbed the corporate ladder, her journalism background giving her a unique edge in understanding consumer behavior.\n\nNow the Director of Market Intelligence for a major information services firm, Kira lives a life of earned comfort in a sleek Hayes Valley condo. Her 2.8-mile commute on the MUNI is a cherished ritual, a time to observe the city's unfolding drama. Her marriage ended amicably five years ago, a casualty of two demanding careers, and she has since cultivated a rich social life with a tight-knit group of friends. They bond over gallery openings, wine tasting trips to Sonoma, and dinners at the city\u2019s newest restaurants.\n\nHaving achieved professional and financial security, Kira feels a pull back to her roots. She has no desire to return to the grind of daily news but aspires to write a non-fiction book exploring the human biases hidden within big data. She envisions a future where she can use her platform to mentor young women of color entering the tech world. Kira Sterling, the observer, has built a successful life by understanding the market; now, she wants to focus on shaping it for the better."
